SIMPLE: outspend
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Outspend
<hw>Out"spend`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
spend more than.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To spend to exhaustion; to spend more than the
limits of; <as>as, he <ex>outspent</ex> the entire discretionary fund
halfway through the year</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outspend</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Outspend
<hw>Out"spend`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Outlay;
expenditure.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A mere <qex>outspend</qex> of savageness.</q> <rj><qau>I.
Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outspin</ent>⟦br⟧
